README.md
    28‚Üí## Features
    30‚Üí- üî• **Hot by default**
    31‚Üí- üî© **Easily Customizable**
    32‚Üí- ‚è≥ **Promise API** - _Automatic loader from a promise_
    33‚Üí- üïä **Lightweight** - _less than 5kb including styles_
    34‚Üí- ‚úÖ **Accessible**
    35‚Üí- ü§Ø **Headless Hooks** - _Create your own with [`useToaster()`](https://react-hot-toast.com/docs/use-toaster)_
    36‚Üí
    37‚Üí## Installation
    39‚Üí#### With pnpm
    41‚Üí```sh
    42‚Üípnpm add react-hot-toast
    43‚Üí```
    44‚Üí
    45‚Üí#### With NPM
    47‚Üí```sh
    48‚Üínpm install react-hot-toast
    49‚Üí```
    50‚Üí
    51‚Üí## Getting Started
    53‚ÜíAdd the Toaster to your app first. It will take care of rendering all notifications emitted. Now you can trigger `toast()` from anywhere!
    54‚Üí
    55‚Üí```jsx
    56‚Üíimport toast, { Toaster } from 'react-hot-toast';
    57‚Üí
    58‚Üíconst notify = () => toast('Here is your toast.');
    59‚Üí
    60‚Üíconst App = () => {
    61‚Üí  return (
    62‚Üí    <div>
    63‚Üí      <button onClick={notify}>Make me a toast</button>
    64‚Üí      <Toaster />
    65‚Üí    </div>
    66‚Üí  );
    67‚Üí};
    68‚Üí```
    69‚Üí
    70‚Üí## Documentation
    72‚ÜíFind the full API reference on [official documentation](https://react-hot-toast.com/docs).
